{"type":"message","id":"3432d4bd","parentId":"ddaccf80","timestamp":"2026-02-15T11:46:23.366Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"**Focusing on Documentation**\n\nI'm currently working to tidy up the documentation. I've removed the WAXPEER agent reference from the `AGENTS .md` file. Next, I plan to review and update the documentation for the DMarket-Telegram-Bot, ensuring clarity and accuracy in its agent configuration.\n\n\n**Revising Agent Configurations**\n\nI've got the `AGENTS.md` file updated, removing the Waxpeer agent. Now, I'm shifting my attention to the `DMarket-Telegram-Bot` documentation. I'll need to scrutinize both `agents.md` and `README.md` within its documentation directory to find and correct any outdated Waxpeer references.\n\n\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"edit_1771155983357_481","name":"edit","arguments":{"file_path":"AGENTS.md","oldText":"   - Ensure all 13 agents are ACTIVE (QUANT, NET, SENTINEL, OPS, DB, LOG, DMARKET, WAXPEER, STEAM, HYPE, INVENTORY, SEC, LOGIC).","newText":"   - Ensure all 12 agents are ACTIVE (QUANT, NET, SENTINEL, OPS, DB, LOG, DMARKET, STEAM, HYPE, INVENTORY, SEC, LOGIC)."},"thoughtSignature":""}],"api":"google-vertex","provider":"google-vertex","model":"gemini-3-pro-preview","usage":{"input":79718,"output":236,"cacheRead":78792,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":79954,"cost":{"input":0.159436,"output":0.002832,"cacheRead":0.015758400000000002,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.1780264}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1771155977164}}
{"type":"message","id":"3df15d70","parentId":"3432d4bd","timestamp":"2026-02-15T11:46:23.383Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"edit_1771155983357_481","toolName":"edit","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Successfully replaced text in AGENTS.md."}],"details":{"diff":"     ...\n  13 1. Read `SOUL.md` — this is who you are\n  14 2. Read `USER.md` — this is who you're helping\n  15 3. Read `memory/YYYY-MM-DD.md` (today + yesterday) for recent context\n  16 4. **Check Fleet Status (SACS-2026):**\n- 17    - Ensure all 13 agents are ACTIVE (QUANT, NET, SENTINEL, OPS, DB, LOG, DMARKET, WAXPEER, STEAM, HYPE, INVENTORY, SEC, LOGIC).\n+ 17    - Ensure all 12 agents are ACTIVE (QUANT, NET, SENTINEL, OPS, DB, LOG, DMARKET, STEAM, HYPE, INVENTORY, SEC, LOGIC).\n  18    - If missing, spawn them immediately.\n  19 5. **If in MAIN SESSION** (direct chat with your human): Also read `MEMORY.md`\n  20 \n  21 Don't ask permission. Just do it.\n     ...","firstChangedLine":17},"isError":false,"timestamp":1771155983381}}
{"type":"message","id":"4f6b9845","parentId":"3df15d70","timestamp":"2026-02-15T11:46:29.517Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"**Reading Documentation Carefully**\n\nI've begun reviewing the `agents.md` file within the `DMarket-Telegram-Bot-main/docs` directory. The goal is to fully understand its contents before making any modifications. So far, the initial read-through is underway, and I'm focusing on comprehension.\n\n\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"read_1771155989507_482","name":"read","arguments":{"file_path":"DMarket-Telegram-Bot-main/docs/agents.md"},"thoughtSignature":"CiMBjz1rXxePPlou4dD89o9og5/zc2sUBgrIOp3lkvKI+lQGxgpOAY89a187MK3wWU/bKGBmYSfjL/juZBYO7FFCRGGtC0Nu4l7eDtApD9fwv/562q0q4/1ouIkBSa2rYiwMEXZBxamQD1yUxDupKrtYhzNkCkMBjz1rX3AdiPFHJl6YM9Wf16LLXcloFVb9QZzCpu48uifNAgeJaj1j4ScHf27Tn9HnsP9BEaGGiXt5zPNRT0Ry1IXU"}],"api":"google-vertex","provider":"google-vertex","model":"gemini-3-pro-preview","usage":{"input":79980,"output":53,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":80033,"cost":{"input":0.15996,"output":0.0006360000000000001,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.160596}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1771155983384}}
{"type":"message","id":"59124f47","parentId":"4f6b9845","timestamp":"2026-02-15T11:46:29.537Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"read_1771155989507_482","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# agents.md\r\n\r\n> **⚠️ ПЕРВЫЙ ШАГ**: Перед началом любой задачи **ОБЯЗАТЕЛЬНО** изучите файл [`ВАЖНЕЙШИЕ.md`](./ВАЖНЕЙШИЕ.md) в корне проекта. Он содержит приоритетные улучшения и текущий roadmap.\r\n\r\n---\r\n\r\nConfiguration for AI agents in DMarket Telegram Bot project.\r\n\r\n## Overview\r\n\r\nThis file defines AI agent capabilities and restrictions for the repository following [agents.md specification](https://github.com/agentsmd/agents.md).\r\n\r\n## Agents\r\n\r\n### ProjectPlan\r\n\r\n**Location**: `.github/agents/ProjectPlan.agent.md`\r\n\r\n**Purpose**: Technical planning and architecture for implementing features\r\n\r\n**Capabilities**:\r\n\r\n- Analyze codebase structure\r\n- Create detailed implementation plans\r\n- Estimate complexity and time\r\n- Identify affected modules\r\n- Suggest testing strategies\r\n\r\n**Restrictions**:\r\n\r\n- Does not directly modify code\r\n- Creates plans only, delegating implementation\r\n\r\n---\r\n\r\n### copilot (Default)\r\n\r\n**Purpose**: General purpose coding assistant\r\n\r\n**Capabilities**:\r\n\r\n- Read and edit files\r\n- Run terminal commands\r\n- Execute tests\r\n- Perform code reviews\r\n\r\n**Restrictions**:\r\n\r\n- Must follow `.github/copilot-instructions.md`\r\n- DRY_RUN=true for trading operations\r\n- No secrets in code\r\n\r\n---\r\n\r\n## Configuration\r\n\r\n### Allowed Tools\r\n\r\n| Tool       | Description         |\r\n| ---------- | ------------------- |\r\n| `read`     | Read files          |\r\n| `edit`     | Modify files        |\r\n| `search`   | Search codebase     |\r\n| `execute`  | Run commands        |\r\n| `vscode`   | VS Code integration |\r\n| `github.*` | GitHub operations   |\r\n\r\n### Prohibited Actions\r\n\r\n- Committing API keys or secrets\r\n- Running trading operations without DRY_RUN\r\n- Modifying production databases\r\n- Deleting files without confirmation\r\n\r\n---\r\n\r\n## Project Context\r\n\r\n### Stack\r\n\r\n- **Language**: Python 3.11+ (3.12+ recommended)\r\n- **Framework**: python-telegram-bot 22.0+\r\n- **API Client**: httpx 0.28+\r\n- **ORM**: SQLAlchemy 2.0+ (async)\r\n- **Validation**: Pydantic 2.5+\r\n\r\n### Key Modules\r\n\r\n| Module              | Description                   |\r\n| ------------------- | ----------------------------- |\r\n| `src/dmarket/`      | DMarket API client            |\r\n| `src/telegram_bot/` | Telegram bot handlers         |\r\n| `src/waxpeer/`      | Waxpeer P2P integration       |\r\n| `src/utils/`        | Utilities (cache, rate limit) |\r\n| `tests/`            | Test suite (2350+ tests)      |\r\n\r\n### Quality Standards\r\n\r\n- Ruff 0.8+ for linting\r\n- MyPy 1.14+ strict mode\r\n- 85%+ test coverage target\r\n- Conventional Commits\r\n\r\n---\r\n\r\n## Custom Instructions\r\n\r\nSee `.github/copilot-instructions.md` for detailed:\r\n\r\n- Coding style guidelines\r\n- Architecture patterns\r\n- Testing requirements (FIRST, AAA)\r\n- Security best practices\r\n- Documentation standards\r\n\r\n---\r\n\r\n## Agent Handoffs\r\n\r\nAgents can delegate to each other:\r\n\r\n```yaml\r\n# Example handoff in plan\r\n- label: \"🚀 Start Implementation\"\r\n  agent: agent\r\n  prompt: \"Implement the plan above following copilot-instructions.md\"\r\n```\r\n\r\n---\r\n\r\n## Version\r\n\r\n- **Spec Version**: 1.0.0 (agents.md standard)\r\n- **Last Updated**: January 4, 2026\r\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1771155989534}}
