{"type":"message","id":"7052e37b","parentId":"7760e854","timestamp":"2026-02-15T11:50:23.126Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"edit_1771156223095_515","toolName":"edit","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Successfully replaced text in DMarket-Telegram-Bot-main/src/dmarket/integrated_arbitrage_scanner.py."}],"details":{"diff":"     ...\n 122 \n 123     def __init__(\n 124         self,\n 125         dmarket_api: DMarketAPI,\n-126         waxpeer_api: WaxpeerAPI,\n 127         steam_api: SteamAPI | None = None,\n 128         min_profit_percent: Decimal = MIN_PROFIT_PERCENT,\n 129         min_liquidity_score: int = MIN_LIQUIDITY_SCORE,\n 130         enable_dmarket_arbitrage: bool = True,\n 131         enable_cross_platform: bool = True,\n 132     ):\n 133         \"\"\"Initialize integrated arbitrage scanner.\n 134 \n 135         Args:\n 136             dmarket_api: DMarket API client\n-137             waxpeer_api: Waxpeer API client\n 138             steam_api: Steam API client (optional)\n 139             min_profit_percent: Minimum profit percentage to consider\n 140             min_liquidity_score: Minimum liquidity score (1-3)\n 141             enable_dmarket_arbitrage: Enable DMarket-only arbitrage\n 142             enable_cross_platform: Enable cross-platform arbitrage\n 143         \"\"\"\n 144         self.dmarket = dmarket_api\n-145         self.waxpeer = waxpeer_api\n 146         self.steam = steam_api\n 147         self.min_profit_percent = min_profit_percent\n 148         self.min_liquidity_score = min_liquidity_score\n 149         self.enable_dmarket_arbitrage = enable_dmarket_arbitrage\n 150         self.enable_cross_platform = enable_cross_platform\n 151 \n 152         # Storage for discovered opportunities and listing targets\n 153         self.opportunities: list[ArbitrageOpportunity] = []\n 154         self.dmarket_only_opportunities: list[dict[str, Any]] = []  # DMarket-only arbitrage\n-155         self.listing_targets: dict[str, WaxpeerListingTarget] = {}  # asset_id -> target\n+152         self.listing_targets: dict[str, Any] = {}  # asset_id -> target\n 156 \n 157         # Tracking\n 158         self.last_scan: datetime | None = None\n 159         self.total_scans: int = 0\n     ...","firstChangedLine":126},"isError":false,"timestamp":1771156223123}}
{"type":"message","id":"01c042e6","parentId":"7052e37b","timestamp":"2026-02-15T11:50:38.274Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"**Eliminating Platform Specifics**\n\nI've just made a significant change. I swapped out `dict[str, WaxpeerListingTarget]` with `dict[str, Any]`. This feels much cleaner now that `WaxpeerListingTarget` is gone. My next step is to remove the Waxpeer-specific logic from `scan_multi_platform`. In fact, I'm now thinking I should probably remove `scan_multi_platform` entirely.\n\n\n**Refactoring Platform Integrations**\n\nI've been focusing on dismantling the Waxpeer integration. I've decided to modify `scan_multi_platform` to only include Steam and DMarket functionality, effectively removing the Waxpeer dependencies. This will involve removing `waxpeer_task`, `waxpeer_prices`, and other related components. I'll need to update `_find_opportunities` as well, since it relies on `waxpeer_prices`.\n\n\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"edit_1771156238150_516","name":"edit","arguments":{"newText":"    async def scan_multi_platform(\n        self, game: str = \"csgo\", limit: int = 50\n    ) -> list[ArbitrageOpportunity]:\n        \"\"\"Scan all platforms and find arbitrage opportunities.\n\n        Args:\n            game: Game code (csgo, dota2, tf2, rust)\n            limit: Maximum items to check per platform\n\n        Returns:\n            List of profitable arbitrage opportunities sorted by profit\n        \"\"\"\n        logger.info(\"starting_multi_platform_scan\", game=game, limit=limit)\n\n        # Fetch prices from all platforms in parallel\n        dmarket_task = self._fetch_dmarket_prices(game, limit)\n        steam_task = self._fetch_steam_prices(game, limit) if self.steam else None\n\n        tasks = [dmarket_task]\n        if steam_task:\n            tasks.append(steam_task)\n\n        results = await asyncio.gather(*tasks, return_exceptions=True)\n\n        dmarket_prices = results[0] if not isinstance(results[0], Exception) else {}\n        steam_prices = results[1] if len(results) > 1 and not isinstance(results[1], Exception) else {}\n\n        logger.info(\n            \"fetched_platform_prices\",\n            dmarket_count=len(dmarket_prices),\n            steam_count=len(steam_prices),\n        )\n\n        # Find opportunities by matching items across platforms\n        opportunities = self._find_opportunities(\n            dmarket_prices, steam_prices, game\n        )\n\n        # Filter by profitability and liquidity\n        filtered = [\n            opp for opp in opportunities\n            if opp.profit_percent >= self.min_profit_percent\n            and opp.liquidity_score >= self.min_liquidity_score\n        ]\n\n        # Sort by profit percentage (best first)\n        filtered.sort(key=lambda x: x.profit_percent, reverse=True)\n\n        # Update tracking\n        self.opportunities = filtered\n        self.last_scan = datetime.now(UTC)\n        self.total_scans += 1\n        self.total_opportunities += len(filtered)\n\n        logger.info(\n            \"scan_complete\",\n            total_opportunities=len(filtered),\n            avg_profit_percent=sum(o.profit_percent for o in filtered) / len(filtered) if filtered else 0,\n        )\n\n        return filtered","oldText":"    async def scan_multi_platform(\n        self, game: str = \"csgo\", limit: int = 50\n    ) -> list[ArbitrageOpportunity]:\n        \"\"\"Scan all platforms and find arbitrage opportunities.\n\n        Args:\n            game: Game code (csgo, dota2, tf2, rust)\n            limit: Maximum items to check per platform\n\n        Returns:\n            List of profitable arbitrage opportunities sorted by profit\n        \"\"\"\n        logger.info(\"starting_multi_platform_scan\", game=game, limit=limit)\n\n        # Fetch prices from all platforms in parallel\n        dmarket_task = self._fetch_dmarket_prices(game, limit)\n        waxpeer_task = self._fetch_waxpeer_prices(game, limit)\n        steam_task = self._fetch_steam_prices(game, limit) if self.steam else None\n\n        tasks = [dmarket_task, waxpeer_task]\n        if steam_task:\n            tasks.append(steam_task)\n\n        results = await asyncio.gather(*tasks, return_exceptions=True)\n\n        dmarket_prices = results[0] if not isinstance(results[0], Exception) else {}\n        waxpeer_prices = results[1] if not isinstance(results[1], Exception) else {}\n        steam_prices = results[2] if len(results) > 2 and not isinstance(results[2], Exception) else {}\n\n        logger.info(\n            \"fetched_platform_prices\",\n            dmarket_count=len(dmarket_prices),\n            waxpeer_count=len(waxpeer_prices),\n            steam_count=len(steam_prices),\n        )\n\n        # Find opportunities by matching items across platforms\n        opportunities = self._find_opportunities(\n            dmarket_prices, waxpeer_prices, steam_prices, game\n        )\n\n        # Filter by profitability and liquidity\n        filtered = [\n            opp for opp in opportunities\n            if opp.profit_percent >= self.min_profit_percent\n            and opp.liquidity_score >= self.min_liquidity_score\n        ]\n\n        # Sort by profit percentage (best first)\n        filtered.sort(key=lambda x: x.profit_percent, reverse=True)\n\n        # Update tracking\n        self.opportunities = filtered\n        self.last_scan = datetime.now(UTC)\n        self.total_scans += 1\n        self.total_opportunities += len(filtered)\n\n        logger.info(\n            \"scan_complete\",\n            total_opportunities=len(filtered),\n            avg_profit_percent=sum(o.profit_percent for o in filtered) / len(filtered) if filtered else 0,\n        )\n\n        return filtered","file_path":"DMarket-Telegram-Bot-main/src/dmarket/integrated_arbitrage_scanner.py"},"thoughtSignature":""}],"api":"google-vertex","provider":"google-vertex","model":"gemini-3-pro-preview","usage":{"input":127289,"o